text: Hazerswoude is a former municipality in the Dutch province of South Holland. It contained the towns of Hazerswoude-Dorp and Hazerswoude-Rijndijk, and the villages of Groenendijk and Bent. Hazerswoude was a separate municipality until 1991, when it became part of Rijneveld. Rijneveld, in 1993 changed in Rijnwoude, has been a part of Alphen aan den Rijn since 2014. ==References== Category:Former municipalities of South Holland Category:Alphen aan den Rijn
